Regarding shared connection vs. multiple connections:

<ul>
<li class="first-item">If you only have one thread, it doesn't matter (obviously).</li>
<li><p class="no-margin">If you do primarily reading...</p><ul>
<li class="first-item">... and the thread count is <= the CPU (core) count: use multiple connections</li>
<li class="last-item">... and you have more threads than CPUs (cores): use shared connection</li>
</ul>

</li>
<li>If you do primarily writing, use a shared connection.</li>
<li class="last-item"><p>If you do about the same amount of reading and writing, use multiple connections.</p></li>
</ul>

